The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                              NATION BRIEFS
                              
	 Chandigarh, Jan. 27 (PTI): Haryana police today said they did not rule out the possibility of the alleged mastermind of a kidney racket having fled the country.          
	Dr Amit Kumar, who owns two hospitals in Gurgaon, is allegedly involved in more than 500 illegal transplants. The police had raided the hospitals yesterday and are preparing a database on Kumar.                  
	Chennai (PTI): A passenger died of a heart attack at Kamaraj domestic airport on Sunday. Somnath Datta, 34, of Tripura had come to board a Calcutta-bound Air Deccan flight. He was in Tamil Nadu to undergo treatment for cancer.                  
	Gurgaon (PTI): A youth died after being accidentally struck by a bullet fired from a revolver at a wedding on Saturday. Gaurav, 20, was on the reception platform along with the bridegroom and some others when a relative fired a shot in the air in celebration.                  
	Guntur (PTI): A police officer was remanded for 14 days on Saturday after he was arrested for allegedly tampering with the date on his birth certificate. Deputy superintendent of police S. Narasaraju is accused of reducing his age by five years.                                                                                                                           
